# AKOS Research Action

Use this rule whenever authoring a `source-ledger.csv`, an external
research synthesis under `docs/wip/intelligence/`, or any research
action that will feed downstream canonical edits or operator
decisions. Codifies operator decision **D-IH-86-FF** (research action
discipline active mint, Wave R+4 C1.6, 2026-05-27). Mechanical
companion to [`RESEARCH_ACTION_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Research/Methodology/canonicals/RESEARCH_ACTION_DISCIPLINE.md).

This rule does **not** define the doctrine — that lives in the
canonical. This rule names the mechanical bar future agents and
operators inherit by default when a research action drives
governance.

## When this rule applies

A research action is in scope for this rule when **any** of:

- A new folder under `docs/wip/intelligence/` is created to host
  prong-shaped or topic-shaped external research that will feed a
  governance commit.
- A `source-ledger.csv` is created or extended in the AKOS workspace.
- A research synthesis (`master-synthesis.md`, `prong-*.md`,
  `research-action-pack.md`, equivalent) is authored to support a
  named downstream decision.
- An external source is added to a tracked research action and that
  source is intended to drive a canonical edit, runbook activation,
  brief authoring, or any other strategic / tactical / operational
  output.

Out of scope:

- One-off operator notes or scratchwork that does not drive a
  governance edit.
- Pre-action substrate audits captured for purely diagnostic reasons.
- Internal-CORPINT research that lives entirely inside
  `docs/wip/intelligence/` and never feeds an external surface or a
  canonical change.

## RULE 1 — Source ledger is mandatory for governance-feeding research (binding)

Every research action that will drive a canonical edit, a runbook
activation, an investor brief, an external deliverable, or any
operator decision MUST carry a `source-ledger.csv` shaped per
[`akos/hlk_research_action.py`](../../akos/hlk_research_action.py)
`COLLABORATOR_SHARE_REGISTRY`-style 15-field schema:

`source_id` (`SRC-` prefix), `prong`, `topic_cluster`,
`source_title_or_owner`, `url` (http(s) or repo-relative `docs/` path),
`format` (one of 9 enum values), `source_category` (OSINT / HUMINT /
SIGINT / CORPINT / MOTINT / TBD per `source_taxonomy.md`),
`source_level` (numeric per `source_taxonomy.md`),
`holistika_reliability_score` (1-5), `external_perceived_credibility_score`
(1-5), `control_confidence_level` (Safe / Euclid / Keter per
`confidence_levels.md`), `decision_use`, `notes`.

The source ledger is the discoverable, queryable, audit-trail-bearing
artifact that the governance commit cites in its
`linked_research_sources` frontmatter. Bare prose synthesis without a
source ledger fails this rule.

## RULE 2 — Operating loop is binding for governance-feeding research

The 8-stage operating loop per
[`RESEARCH_ACTION_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Research/Methodology/canonicals/RESEARCH_ACTION_DISCIPLINE.md)
§3 must be walked in order: **ingest** -> **rate** -> **rank** ->
**synthesize** -> **govern** -> **implement** -> **test** ->
**iterate**. Each stage produces a durable artifact (ingested
sources / ledger row / ranked priority / synthesis prong / inline
ratify gate / canonical edit / validator run / next-cycle entry).
Skipping a stage produces one of the anti-patterns named in
[`RESEARCH_ACTION_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Research/Methodology/canonicals/RESEARCH_ACTION_DISCIPLINE.md)
§5 (research-as-ornament, confidence drift, premature governance,
folder ambiguity, ERP/KB invisibility).

## RULE 3 — Run the validator self-test at every pre_commit (binding)

[`scripts/validate_research_action.py --self-test`](../../scripts/validate_research_action.py)
verifies the Pydantic SSOT chassis (`ResearchSourceRow` +
`ResearchSourceLedgerSummary` + 5 enum frozensets) at every
`py scripts/verify.py pre_commit` invocation via:

- [`config/verification-profiles.json`](../../config/verification-profiles.json)
  `pre_commit.steps`: `validate_research_action_self_test` (wired
  at C1.6).
- [`scripts/release-gate.py`](../../scripts/release-gate.py):
  `run_research_action_self_test()` advisory wiring.

The self-test cost is sub-1s. Per-ledger validation runs at
research-action authoring cadence: `py scripts/validate_research_action.py
--source-ledger <path>` fires when a ledger lands or extends.

## RULE 4 — Paired SOP+runbook contract honored

Per [`akos-executable-process-catalog.mdc`](akos-executable-process-catalog.mdc)
Rule 1:

- **AC-HUMAN** — a human OR an AIC role_owner (Research Director + KM
  Officer; PMO interim absorption when those roles are unstaffed) can
  walk the 8-stage operating loop following
  [`SOP-RESEARCH_ACTION_001.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Research/Methodology/canonicals/SOP-RESEARCH_ACTION_001.md)
  without invoking the runbook.
- **AC-AUTOMATION** — the runbook validates ledger schema
  mechanically: `--self-test` mode in pre_commit, `--source-ledger
  <path>` mode at authoring time.

Both surfaces are SSOT for the same discipline; neither supersedes
the other.

## RULE 5 — INFO ramp posture (binding from D-IH-86-FF)

The validator launches at INFO advisory for the per-ledger sweep at
Wave R+4 C1.6. Promotion to FAIL gates on:

1. 3+ research actions across 2+ Holistika areas apply the discipline
   cleanly with no schema findings.
2. Cross-area audit pass at quarterly cadence with operator sign-off.
3. Operator-explicit ramp-promotion decision row (D-IH-86-FF
   successor, e.g., `D-IH-86-FF-V2`).

The self-test stays at FAIL ramp permanently (any chassis regression
breaks pre_commit). Per-ledger schema findings start INFO and ramp
per the gates above.

## When this rule does NOT apply

- Operator scratchwork or in-session notes without downstream
  governance intent.
- Pre-Wave-R+4 research material that pre-dates the discipline mint;
  the bar is forward-only from D-IH-86-FF (2026-05-27).
- Intelligence material that lives entirely under
  `docs/wip/intelligence/` and never feeds a canonical edit (governed
  by INTELLIGENCE_DISCIPLINE_CHARTER instead).

